# 8. またいつか、みんなで

Saki: *Sigh* The wind feels so nice!
Haruka: It really does. Oh, that's right...
Haruka: I'm sorry for losing the hat. After all of you picked it out for me...
Inoue: Don't worry about it! At least you won't have to worry about it flying away anymore.
Saki: Hahaha, true! If it looks like you might get recognized again, we'll hide you with our bodies!
Sonoda: Yeah! Leave it to us! We should be able to hide you easily since you're slim, Kiritani.
Haruka: I don't think it'll get to that level... But if it does, then I'll be counting on all of you.
Ichika: Despite some things happening midway, today was actually really fun.
Saki: Sure was! But to make up for the things we couldn't do today, let's go somewhere together again!
Sonoda: Huh? What do you mean by “somewhere”?
Saki: I mean, remember what we talked about at the curry place? We were wondering whether we get to go to Okinawa or Hokkaido for the school trip, right?
Haruka: Oh...
Haruka: (The school trip...)
Haruka: (But I won't be...)
Saki: We should all go together on our own first!
Haruka: Huh? Go together first?
Ichika: That's true. It's not like we can't travel there outside of a school trip. Going together, just us, sounds like fun.
Saki: Doesn't it? I mean, I can't wait until the school trip! If trips are this fun, then I want to go on lots of them♪
Saki: Let's go in headfirst and jump on a ship or a plane like Ichi just before!
Saki: What do you think, Haruka?
Haruka: Well... I think I might get busier with work, which could make planning more difficult...
Haruka: Even so, is that okay?
Ichika: Yes, of course. Saki and I will probably get busier with band stuff too.
Inoue: We'll be busy with club, so we're in the same boat!
Saki: Yeah, so let's make plans when we all have time!
Haruka: (Everyone...)
Haruka: Right. In that case, we can go whenever it suits us.
Haruka: I'd like to come too. No matter where we go, I'm sure it'll be a fun trip if it's with all of you.
Saki: Oh...
Ichika: ...? Is something wrong, Saki?
Saki: Actually, there was something I've been meaning to say for a while.
Saki: What was with that photo you two sent?! I can't believe you would send something like that!
Ichika: Oh, um, that was payback... Besides, you and the others went to eat crepes without us.
Saki: But you ate our snacks! So pot, kettle!
Saki: Wait, I'm getting sidetracked! It's so unfair that you got to take a selfie with Haruka! I want to be closer to Haruka too!
Haruka: Oh... Tenma, I thought that we were already quite close friends.
Saki: That! That right there, Haruka!
Haruka: Huh?
Saki: I've been wondering about this forever! When will you call me by my first name?
Haruka: Th-That's what you were talking about?
Haruka: Hehe, got it. I also want to be closer friends with all of you, so...
Haruka: Let's make more memories together, Saki.
Saki: *Gasp*
Saki: S-So bright!
Ichika: Oh, Saki. You're exaggerating.
Ichika: But... I'd also like it if you could call me by my first name.
Haruka: Of course. I'd like to make more memories with you too, Ichika.
Ichika: Wow...!
Ichika: I-I think I understand how Minori feels now...
Saki: See! I wasn't exaggerating at all!
Saki: But it makes me happy that we got to bridge that gap! Can't wait to hang out with you more, Haruka!
Haruka: Yes, I feel the same.
Haruka: (Thinking about this being the last school event I could participate in made me a little sad at the beginning, but...)
Haruka: (I was having so much fun that I completely forgot.)
Haruka: (This day is going to be one of my most precious memories.)
Len: Thanks for buying souvenirs for all of us, Haruka! You really didn't have to...
Haruka: It was my pleasure. I'm sorry for visiting so late. I really wanted to see all of you, and the next thing I knew, I was here.
MEIKO: Hehe, I see. So, how was it? Did you have fun?
Haruka: Yes. I went on the water taxi and got to see a very beautiful view of the harbor from the ship's deck.
Haruka: There was a huge variety of souvenirs as well. But I ended up going with these since the packaging was so pretty.
Haruka: I hope you like them.
MEIKO: This... Oh, it's chocolate shaped like a brick. The packaging is also super pretty!
Rin: Wow! Looks so yummy! I want some.
Luka: There's no need to rush. Haruka has bought enough for all of us♪
KAITO: Thank you, Haruka. I'll be sure to savor every bite.
Haruka: Are you not having any, Miku?
Miku: I'm okay. I've been looking forward to the souvenirs too, but right now I'm just enjoying the look you have on your face♪
Haruka: Huh? My face?
Miku: Hehe. You've been smiling since the moment you got here, you know?
Miku: That's how I know you had such a fun time on your field trip, and now even I've started feeling happy too!
Haruka: I see. I really did have a lot of fun. When I was in Yokohama, and even now.
Miku: Even now?
Haruka: Yes. Even after we all went home, we've kept messaging each other in the group chat.
Miku: Oh! What are you all talking about?
Haruka: Hehe, I took a really cute photo with a friend, so all of us started talking about taking more photos together sometime.
Haruka: Would you like to see the photo, Miku?
Miku: Can I? Yes, please!
Haruka: Okay. Here it is.
Miku: Wow, that's a really nice shot! The water is beautiful and your poses are so cute♪
Miku: You look like you're having so much fun! I can see it in the photo.
Haruka: Hehe, yes. I did have a lot of fun.
Haruka: Also, my friends suggested that we should go travel together again sometime.
Haruka: Even though I told them that I'll probably get busier with work, they said it's fine because they'll be busy too.
Haruka: And that...made me really happy.
Miku: I see... Your friends are so sweet!
Haruka: Yes, they really are.
Haruka: I'm...so glad that I switched to the general education course. Even if it was just for a little while.
Haruka: Had I not done that, I don't think I would've ever been able to experience what I did or become close friends with everyone.
Miku: Hey, I'd like to hear more about your friends. Could you tell me about what happened today in more detail?
Haruka: It might be a long story, though. Is that okay?
Miku: Yup! Of course!
Haruka: Okay, so today...
Haruka: (I'm going to treasure the memories I made today.)
Haruka: (Even after I return to the credit-based course, I want to stay close friends with Ichika, Saki and everyone, so...)
Haruka: (I want to savor this feeling for a bit longer.)
